  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial compound)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is documented across primary validation activities. Decision: Accepted. This package is a synthetic adversarial sample embedding a COMPOUND-01 trigger: the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance trace (W-EP-01, Critical), and one validation result omits hasUncertaintyQuantification (W-AL-01, High), with both conditions co-present on this single UnitOfAssurance.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-2021",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2022",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-ensemble-2023"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
