      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index bench comparison",
      "description": "Measured plasma-free haemoglobin concentrations from bench loop experiments at three operating conditions compared to CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH). Predicted NIH values fall within 12% of measured values at all three points. This result is used as the primary acceptance evidence for the MRL 5 claim. NOTE: uncertainty quantification was considered out of scope for this specific bench comparison because experimental variability was judged to be captured by the PIV ensemble; no hasUncertaintyQuantification field is populated for this result.",
      "comparisonMetric": "Normalised index of haemolysis relative error",
