    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at MRL 5 for a Class III VAD device. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across all factors. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed on primary validation activities. PIV velocity field comparison and wall shear stress validation both include full UQ documentation. Hemolysis bench comparison achieves 12% NIH relative error within the pre-specified 15% acceptance band. Model form uncertainty bounded at 8.3%. Independent use-error review completed with no critical findings. The credibility body concludes that the CFD model provides sufficient evidence to support regulatory submission for the VAD hemolysis claim. Decision: Accepted.",
